  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 220°C. Finely slice the shallot. Halve the cherry tomatoes. Finely chop the chilli. Grate the garlic. Chop the rosemary and drain the potatoes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Lay out a large sheet of parchment per portion, facing portrait. Arrange the shallots, cherry tomatoes and potatoes on the bottom half of the paper leaving a 10cm gap between the food and the edge closest to you. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. If you’re scaling up for more people, just use a parchment-lined baking tray and a tight foil lid instead. Cooking times might vary, so keep an eye on it."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pat the cod fillets dry with kitchen paper and season on both sides. Pop them on top of the veg, then spoon over the grated garlic. Dot the butter over the fish, then scatter with the chopped chilli and rosemary."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Fold the top half of the baking paper over the food then fold the outside edges over each other to seal (like a cornish pasty), creating a steam-tight parcel."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Transfer to a baking tray and bake for 18–20 mins, depending on the thickness of your cod. Serve straight from the foil."
    }
  ],
